11.2.10 Stretch Goals

Use the jsPsychKeyboardResponse plugin to add a final screen to our experiment that says “The experiment is finished. Thank you for completing our study!”. Make sure the choices is set to “NO_KEYS” so they can’t advance any further.
Use the jsPsychKeyboardResponse plugin to add a screen between our study and test phase that says “You are now about to begin the memory test phase. Press any key to begin.”
Add a new CSS class called fixationStyle and apply it only to the fixation trial to make the fixation bigger (48pt).
Use the button_html function to Style the OLD and NEW buttons so that they are different colors.

12.3 Audio Plugins
Audio stimuli are essential for language research, auditory perception studies, and providing feedback to participants. The jsPsychAudioKeyboardResponse plugin (https://www.jspsych.org/v8/plugins/audio-keyboard-response/) handles audio playback while collecting keyboard responses.

